\section{Conclusion}
This is the conclusion section.

\end{document}
```

In this example, when you compile the document, LaTeX will automatically generate a table of contents that includes the section titles and page numbers. The `\tableofcontents` command should be placed where you want the TOC to appear in your document.

If you want to customize the TOC, you can use various options provided by `tocloft`. For example, to change the font size or formatting of the TOC, you can use the `\cftsett` command:

